==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Saw-set
<hw>Saw"-set`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An instrument used
to set or turn the teeth of a saw a little sidewise, that they may make
a kerf somewhat wider than the thickness of the blade, to prevent
friction; -- called also <altname>saw-wrest</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sawtooth</ent>⟦br⟧
